gaudit - proof of concept security audits using libvirt/libguestfs

INSTALLATION
    This installation information is assuming that the host (or machine running 
the KVM hypervisor) is Fedora version 16 or higher running on the x86_64
architecture.

Installation is as simple as running the following command as root:
    yum -y localinstall gaudit-0.1-1.fc16.x86_64.rpm --nogpgcheck

At this point installation is complete and documentation can be found with
the following command:
    man 8 gaudit

Or simply run the companion program and follow the on screen instructions:
    gaudit-tui
